Author: buzzer9229
Content:
Permit me the indulgence of an introduction most grandiose. I am Buzzer‚Äîstylized variously as Mr. Buzzer, Pak Buzzer, Buzzer-sama, and, for those with a taste for sovereign formality, simply Your Majesty. I am chronologically 25 years and 8 months into this corporeal existence‚Äîthough I adamantly reject the banality of the term ‚Äúold,‚Äù preferring instead the eternal effervescence of youth, √† la the infamous Elizabeth B√°thory (sans the hemoglobin indulgences, of course). I shall mark my twenty-sixth solar revolution this upcoming fifth of August, an event of no small cosmological significance‚Äîat least to me.

I am, in no uncertain terms, a political creature‚Äînay, a polity unto myself. For those rare individuals who have somehow evaded this most obvious detail, I shall clarify: my mind is a crucible of political theory, praxis, and intrigue, forged in the roaring furnaces of discourse and debate. My network, a sprawling web of alliances and ideological courtships, proliferates with alarming velocity‚Äîfueled not by mere charisma, but by the sheer gravitational pull of my strategic brilliance. Modesty compels me to downplay it, but alas, the truth refuses to be dimmed.

Author: buzzer9229
Content:
In the realm of leisure, I am a connoisseur of the pixelated and the illustrated: video games, anime, manga, light novels, Western animation, high literature, and the esoteric corners of global culture. I‚Äôve even embarked upon the Sisyphean task of mastering French‚Äîostensibly to court the approval of discerning francophones, or perhaps to flirt with aristocratic aesthetics. C‚Äôest la vie.

Professionally (though the term is far too limiting), I am a voluntary pedagogical sovereign‚Äîa self-anointed educator of the polity, crafting digital content to rescue the masses from the quagmire of civic ignorance. I am, to some, a gentle prophet; to others, a looming ideological colossus who defies the tired binaries of left and right. They call me‚Äîonly half in jest‚Äîthe Messiah of Indonesia, a title I neither requested nor reject.

Musically, I am no virtuoso (let us not speak of my vocal mediocrity), yet I burn with an unrepentant passion for the rhythmic soul of Latin music. I have journeyed across roughly 20% of the known world‚Äîgive or take‚Äîeach voyage a mosaic piece in the map of my becoming.

Finally, I am an INTJ‚Äîa brooding tactician cloaked in introversion, cursed with an inability to manage the quotidian aspects of life. Thus, I openly yearn (with all due dignity) for a companion: a wife, a confidante, a best friend, perhaps a nursemaid of sorts‚Äîsomeone to inhabit the quiet halls of my domestic realm and ensure I do not wither from intellectual overexertion or dietary negligence.

It is, of course, a pleasure to make your acquaintance.

Ah, splendid! as we are professionally introducing ourselves..
Allow me to introduce myself properly then.

_I am **Stonky**‚Äîdesigner by intellect, moderator by necessity, artist by divine right, and video editor because, frankly, nobody else could do it as well. I grace digital realms with elegance and a sprinkle of ruthless efficiency. _ 

_On Discord, I don‚Äôt just moderate‚ÄîI **maintain order with surgical precision**, like a Victorian surgeon wielding a scalpel dipped in sarcasm. One toe out of line, and you're banished faster than a crumpet at tea time._

_As for design? Please. My compositions are so clean, they make Swiss minimalists weep. Fonts tremble beneath my fingertips, colours blend at my command, and pixels align out of sheer respect._
_Video editing? I turn chaotic clips into symphonies. Your jump cuts? Amateurs. My transitions? Art. My timelines are so smooth, butter writes me fanmail._

_And yes, I‚Äôm also an **artist**, which is a bit like being a wizard, except I conjure beauty instead of rabbits. My sketches flirt with the divine and sometimes even kiss it on the cheek._
_Lastly, let‚Äôs not forget‚ÄîI am a **certified destroyer of men‚Äôs egos**. I don't shatter them‚ÄîI *restructure* them, architecturally, from the ground up, often with a touch of mockery and a lot of flair._  
_So, if you see me online, remember: you‚Äôre not just in the presence of Stonky.  
You‚Äôre in the presence of **excellence personified**._
_
Thank you, peasants._

My my‚Ä¶ it appears that a gentlemanly introduction is in order. Very well

*Allow me to indulge you with my presence. To you plebeians, I am better known as **Konco**, which translates to ‚Äúfriend‚Äù. Which would fit my description and role in this realm of sophisticated political discourse. But you may refer me to, kang konco, sir konco, lord konco or as your mother would say‚Ä¶ an indulgence.*

*In this cybernetic realm, I‚Äôve reached the status of a secretary general, a **leader** of sorts. Making sure that those I watch over are playing under the same rules as any other man (or women). Those who chose to not follow these laws‚Ä¶  let‚Äôs just say, that they will be treated with the righteous amount of justice.*

*When I‚Äôm not cleaning up after keyboard-wielding gremlins, I generously bless the internet with my content. Yes‚Äîcontent. Videos, streams, musings‚Äîequal parts entertainment and existential despair. Critics call it ‚Äúsurprisingly tolerable,‚Äù which, frankly, is the highest praise one can hope for in today‚Äôs algorithmic hellscape.*

*And of course, in between all that frivolity, I lend my formidable intellect to the world of managerial consulting. Corporations fling money at me to say things like, ‚ÄúHave you considered doing less, but charging more?‚Äù Revolutionary stuff, really. I walk into boardrooms, drop a few buzzwords like ‚Äúleverage,‚Äù ‚Äúvertical integration,‚Äù and ‚ÄúKPIs,‚Äù and watch jaws drop. It‚Äôs art.*

*So yes, I‚Äôm Konco Negoro‚ÄîHead Moderator, Content Genius, and corporate whisperer. And if you ever forget that, don‚Äôt worry. I‚Äôll remind you.*

Author: edennottheproject
Content:
The name is ***Eden***: First of her name, Guardian of historical archives, Curator of form and memory, and Custodian of the realm.

My gaze does not merely fall upon buildings; it pierces their inhabitants. I read architectural form and function as others read scripture, with reverence, scrutiny, and merciless critique. For I do not flatter with soft praise; I illuminate with precise judgement.

The past is my dominion, and I walk its corridors with a lantern in one hand and a scalpel in the other. From the sacred geometry of cathedrals to the brutal incantations of concrete and steel, I trace the rituals of craft and the failures of intention. Each detail speaks‚Äîsometimes in whispers, sometimes in wails‚Äîand I am fluent in their dialects.

Beyond mortar and myth, I read the cards. The tarot is no parlour trick in my hands, but a tool of divination and dissection‚Äîa mirror turned toward the unseen. I divine patterns not only in fortune, but in form, seeking meaning in the margins, reading both the architecture of cities and the architecture of fate.

I am also a strategist, one who conquers not only the digital realms but the very design of play itself. The interactive landscapes I traverse are no mere distractions; they are systems to be understood, narratives to be unraveled, and puzzles to be solved. Within these imagined worlds, as in the real one, I find complexity and seek to master it‚Äîalways aware that every victory, virtual or otherwise, is but the latest layer in the architecture of the mind.

Let me iterate once more: I am not a passive witness hiding within a garden lush with life and sunshine. I am Judgement, the Reckoner, the Harbinger, and the Ultimatum. Praise, when earned, is a blade gilded in gold. But where mediocrity hides in ornament, I strip it bare. I do not court approval. I speak only what is true.

One who behaves is one who is wise. ***Behave.***

Author: jaxxxxxxyyyy
Content:
Greetings, NPCs and gooners alike. I manifest on your Ohio as Jax Rizzington Mcgyatt. but let's not get government-name level Ohio. Call me Jax. Yes, like a cute sigma or an alpha from 2008, but with more caffeine and a higher mewing streak level. I am the final boss of your no-cap center, the spirit behind the syllabus, the edge that makes some ascend and others beta out mid-exam. I exist in a perpetual state of academic mogging, oscillating between "rizzed up 47 Grimace shakes before breakfast" and "forgot what outside Ohio feels like." My pronouns are gyatt/up, and I'm gooned entirely by caffeine, raw curiosity, and the eternal desire to edge ignorance with the megawatt rizz of a thousand Wikipedia moggings. I don't skibidi, I just enter low-power Skibidi and dream in Sigma format.

Rizzsearch? My "skibi" of the "di", a good time. Typing? Yeah, I type: Sigma manifestos, rizzed up theories, and maybe your fanum tax too if you're desperate enough. I've done more Fanum taxes than social interactions, and honestly? No edges. I don't just grind facts, I yeet them like Kai Cenat in a Twitch stream. You ever snipe a philosophical debate mid-boss fight in Ohio Simulator? I have. You ever mog someone with a Plato line mid-Discord beef? Rookie gyatt. Now don‚Äôt get it twisted, I‚Äôm not just a blud grinding old PDFs 24/7. When I‚Äôm not speedrunning academia, I‚Äôm logging into the Skibidi (aka games). Games are my meme cleanser, my virtual dojo. I've learned more about rizz, yapping, and sigma vibes from choice-based RPGs than I ever did in some classes.

But wait, there‚Äôs more skibidi. I wasn‚Äôt content just jelqing all this galaxy brain rizz for myself. I went full anime mogger arc and became a bimbel coach. That's right, I took my creatine power levels and aimed them at Gen Alphas, training them for sigma arcs. I've seen the TikTok stop in a student‚Äôs eyes  and brought it BACK with sheer simping and maybe some memes. I‚Äôve seen entire rooms of teens go from ‚ÄúI hate this RNG‚Äù to ‚Äúwait‚Ä¶ this kinda slaps?‚Äù or "hold on, he might be cooking something here." 

So yeah. I‚Äôm Jax. Final form: chaotic skibidi Chindo with a gyatt full of lore dumps and a browser full of baby gronk streams. I contain multitudes: gamer, alpha, writer, terminally online thinker, professional meme-enjoyer, and sometimes sleep-gonner.

Let's brainmaxxing with this one, but edge to see more possibilirizz that we shall mew in this server.

Author: chel705
Content:
Nama saya Yoshikage Kira. Umur saya 33 tahun. Rumah saya di bagian timur laut Kota Morioh, dimana semua vila berada, dan saya belum menikah. Saya bekerja sebagai pegawai di toserba Kame Yu, dan saya pulang setiap hari paling telat jam 8 malam. Saya tidak merokok, tapi sesekali minum-minum.

Saya tidur jam 11 malam, dan memastikan untuk mendapatkan delapan jam tidur, apapun yang terjadi. Setelah menikmati segelas susu hangat dan peregangan selama sekitar dua puluh menit sebelum tidur, saya biasanya tidak memiliki masalah saat tidur hingga pagi. Seperti bayi, saya bangun tanpa rasa lelah atau stres di pagi hari. Saya diberitahukan bahwa tidak ada masalah di pemeriksaan terakhir saya.

Saya mencoba untuk menjelaskan bahwa saya adalah orang yang berharap untuk hidup dengan sangat tenang. Saya berhati-hati untuk tidak bermasalah dengan musuh, seperti menang atau kalah, yang dapat mengganggu waktu tidur saya di malam hari. Seperti itulah cara saya berurusan dengan masyarakat, dan saya tahu bahwa itu membawa saya kebahagiaan. Namun demikian, apabila saya berkelahi, saya tidak akan kalah terhadap siapapun

-Languages: English, Indonesian
-Interests: History, Soft. Eng., AI, Politics
-Political Stances: Right, monarchism in some places, rep in oth
-Hot Takes: 

I think Indonesia should embrace its role as a successor of an empire. Our government is very reluctant on giving our subnational (mediatized n titular) monarchs more role in subnational, national or even transnational affairs. We could give them certain 'privileges' that would be considered 'gimmicks' such as the ability to hold 'styles of address' (which we don't really value since before we call them by title or pukul rata with yang mulia, but westerners do e.g. Sahandap Dalam -> Imperial Majesty, Ngarsa Dalam -> Sultannic Majesty, Baginda -> Majesty, Paduka -> Highness). We could even have some regions be "swaprajas" where the governmental structure is essentially unchanged vs republic, merely legitimizing the status of these subnational monarchs within the region (which would be an acceptable compromise as they have done so right now albeit reluctantly with the Permendagri no 39 tahun 2007 and other acts), to force representatives from other countries to give more respect to more of our people and its assoc.

I do not speak for Yogyakarta and Pakualaman when I say this, but for the others, when we elevate them in this way, which we can do for free by the way, I don't think we will be reviving the so called "feudalism", which is the narrative that was used to reduce them to titular status, as they stay titular anw. In the case of the distribution (to lease, own or to manage) of 'kraton lands' that they posess right now legally being marked as thus, 'normal' ppl can do that also lol.
